<para styleclass="Normal"><para styleclass="Normal">
    Classes helpers and record helpers have been introduced since Delphi
    2007. The initial purpose is to allow developers to extend a class
    without change the original structure.
  </para><para style="margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 5px"><table rowcount="2" colcount="1" styleclass="Note Table"><thead><td style="background-color:#EFEFF7"><para><image src="note.png" /><text styleclass="Column" style="font-size:8pt">Note</text></para></td></thead><tr><td><para styleclass="Normal" style="margin-top:8px;margin-bottom:8px;margin-left:8px;margin-right:5px">
    A class helper type may not declare instance data, but class fields
    are allowed.
  </para></td></tr></table></para><para style="margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 5px"><table rowcount="2" colcount="1" styleclass="Note Table"><thead><td style="background-color:#EFEFF7"><para><image src="alert_caution.gif" /><text styleclass="Column" style="font-size:8pt">Warning</text></para></td></thead><tr><td><para styleclass="Normal" style="margin-top:8px;margin-bottom:8px;margin-left:8px;margin-right:5px">
    Class helpers and record helpers are not intended to be a design tool
    in Delphi. It is some kind of "patching" technology.
  </para></td></tr></table></para><para styleclass="Normal">
    If you want to use these helpers, just uses the Spring.Helpers
    namespace in the target unit.
  </para></para>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</para>
